 This install applies to "Agony" © 1992 Psygnosis.

 This install requires WHDLoad and RawDIC to be in the path. Both can be found
 in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem and 1.0 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 version 2.1 (02.11.2019) done by ross:
 - Added small delay after intro and before game start, in "Alestes metamorphoses into an owl" screen.
 - Fixed: On AGA this game suffered from gfx glitches visible on real machine and high res monitor

 version 2.0 (25.12.2018) done by JOTD:
 - added infinite lives trainer
 - added full power trainer: all magic weapons available, fully powered, infinite lives
 - added switch to skip introduction (only works in PAL mode)
  (without buttonwait, the game starts immediately. Note that this can be
   achieved by holding fire button when booting in the original, also note that
   it crashes NTSC version, like it did when holding fire in the original !! didn't fix that)
 - full slave rewrite, adapted to whdload 17
 - better highscore handling
 
 version 1.3 (15.05.05) done by JOTD
 - 2-button joystick support (displays spells like spacebar)
 - reworked install package & readme

 version 1.2 (2004)
 - RawDIC imager

 version 1.1 (2003)
 - Display bugs fixed (thanks Psygore for the hint!)

 version 1.0 (2002) done by JOTD:
 - initial WHDLoad release
 - Supports both PAL and NTSC versions
 - Fixed access faults (made invincible ennemies on 32 bit CPUs!)
 - HELP skips to next level
 - Quits with QUITKEY key.
 - Now works with caches (the music had problems)
 - Relocated decunch routine in fastmem for light speed loading
 - Hiscore load/save from HD
 - BUTTONWAIT tooltype allows you to listen to inter-level music
 - Documentation included (french/english)
 - Nice icons by Chris Vella, Frank & Exoticons
 - Manual included
 - Source code included

 version 0.x (1997) dony by JOTD & Harry
 - initial JST release

 Note: This one was hard work for me due to the disk loading routine & encryption.
 (I had to ask for help to Harry who wrote a clean system friendly disk imager)
 Anyway I had my revenge in the title screen :-) (only in PAL version)
